---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Yahuah's Feast Calendar — Nazaryah"
  description="The mo'edim of the Father — set into the sun, the moon, and the stars on day four of creation, written in the heavens for every believer to see."
>
  <main class="cal-landing">

    <!-- ──────────────── TEASER BANNER ──────────────── -->
    <a href="/calendar/today" class="today-banner">
      <div class="today-banner-inner">
        <div class="today-banner-side roman">
          <span class="today-banner-label">Your phone says</span>
          <span class="today-banner-value" id="banner-roman-date">&mdash;</span>
        </div>

        <div class="today-banner-cta">
          <div class="today-banner-cta-eyebrow">Today</div>
          <div class="today-banner-cta-line">Which one are you on?</div>
          <div class="today-banner-cta-arrow">See both calendars &rarr;</div>
        </div>

        <div class="today-banner-side yahs">
          <span class="today-banner-label">The heavens say</span>
          <span class="today-banner-value" id="banner-yahs-date">&mdash;</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </a>

    <!-- ──────────────── HERO ──────────────── -->
    <section class="cal-hero">
      <p class="cal-eyebrow with-rules">Feast Calendar</p>
      <h1 class="cal-title">Yahuah's Appointed Times</h1>
      <p class="cal-subtitle">The mo'edim of the Father &mdash; set into the sun, the moon, and the stars on day four of creation, written in the heavens for every believer to see.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- ──────────────── 3 LUMINARY CARDS ──────────────── -->
    <section class="cal-block">
      <div class="cal-section-head">
        <p class="cal-eyebrow with-rules">Before the Calendar</p>
        <h2 class="cal-section-title">The Lights Yahuah Made</h2>
        <p class="cal-section-subtitle">What the sun, moon, and stars are, what they were made for, and why the One who made them is the only One worth the credit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="luminary-grid">

        <a href="/studies/the-sun-in-scripture" class="luminary-card lum-sun">
          <p class="card-label">Foundation &middot; The Greater Light</p>
          <h3>The Sun in Scripture</h3>
          <p>What the sun represents, where its light comes from, and why it is not the Son. The greater light, the Father's office, and the lamp that will one day be retired.</p>
          <span class="read-link">Read the Study &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/studies/the-moon-in-scripture" class="luminary-card lum-moon">
          <p class="card-label">Foundation &middot; The Lesser Light</p>
          <h3>The Moon in Scripture</h3>
          <p>What the moon represents, where her light comes from, and the bride's witness in the heavens. Levanah, the white one &mdash; the lamp of the night who marks the months.</p>
          <span class="read-link">Read the Study &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/studies/the-stars-in-scripture" class="luminary-card lum-stars">
          <p class="card-label">Foundation &middot; The Host of Heaven</p>
          <h3>The Stars in Scripture</h3>
          <p>What the stars represent, how they witness the year, and the bright morning Star Himself. The host of heaven &mdash; Yahuah's army of messengers marching in unison around the pole.</p>
          <span class="read-link">Read the Study &rarr;</span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ──────────────── DIVIDER ──────────────── -->
    <div class="cal-divider">
      <span class="glyph">&#9670; &#9670; &#9670;</span>
    </div>

    <!-- ──────────────── 12 CATEGORY CARDS ──────────────── -->
    <section class="cal-block">
      <div class="cal-section-head">
        <p class="cal-eyebrow with-rules">The Twelve Categories</p>
        <h2 class="cal-section-title">Walking Through the Calendar</h2>
        <p class="cal-section-subtitle">From the foundations of the appointed times, to the feasts themselves, to walking them out today.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="category-grid">

        <a href="/calendar/foundation" class="cat-card cat-card-active">
          <p class="roman">I</p>
          <h3>Foundation</h3>
          <p>The mo'edim of Yahuah, the Hebrew word that names them, and Creation's calendar set against man's.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/whose-calendar" class="cat-card cat-card-active">
          <p class="roman">II</p>
          <h3>Whose Calendar?</h3>
          <p>How Rome's Gregorian system replaced Yahuah's heavens, and where the rabbinic calendar drifted from Torah.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-day" class="cat-card cat-card-active">
          <p class="roman">III</p>
          <h3>The Day</h3>
          <p>The 12-hour day of light, dawn to dusk &mdash; the Babylonian sundown tradition, and the Roman midnight lie that crept into the church.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-week" class="cat-card cat-card-active">
          <p class="roman">IV</p>
          <h3>The Week &amp; Sabbath</h3>
          <p>The lunar Sabbath cycle that resets every new moon, the perpetual sign Yahuah called <em>olam</em>, and the continuous Roman week Constantine layered Sunday on top of.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-month" class="cat-card cat-card-active">
          <p class="roman">V</p>
          <h3>The Month</h3>
          <p>Chodesh meaning renewed, the new moon throughout Scripture, and how the moon is rightly determined.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/the-year" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">VI</p>
          <h3>The Year</h3>
          <p>Aviv as the first month, what aviv actually means, the barley witness in Israel, and the equinox error.</p>
          <span class="study-count">4 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/mazzaroth" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">VII</p>
          <h3>The Mazzaroth</h3>
          <p>Yahuah's gospel written in the stars, separated from zodiac corruption, and the banners of the twelve tribes.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/seven-moedim" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">VIII</p>
          <h3>The Seven Moedim</h3>
          <p>Pesach, Hag HaMatzot, Bikkurim, Shavuot, Yom Teruah, Yom Kippur, Sukkot, and Shemini Atzeret.</p>
          <span class="study-count">8 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/jubilee" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">IX</p>
          <h3>Sabbatical &amp; Jubilee</h3>
          <p>The shemitah seventh-year rest, the fiftieth-year liberty, and Daniel's seventy weeks in the Jubilee cycle.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/false-feasts" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">X</p>
          <h3>False Feasts Exposed</h3>
          <p>Christmas, Easter, Lent, Halloween, and the principle of Deuteronomy 12:30&ndash;32 that condemns them all.</p>
          <span class="study-count">4 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/salvation-first" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">XI</p>
          <h3>Salvation First</h3>
          <p>Salvation through Yahushua alone, Torah obedience as fruit, and the false grace-versus-Law dichotomy.</p>
          <span class="study-count">3 Studies</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/practical" class="cat-card cat-card-pending">
          <p class="roman">XII</p>
          <h3>Practical Observance</h3>
          <p>Sighting the new moon, tracking the aviv barley, a feast calendar template, and family observance.</p>
          <span class="study-count">4 Studies</span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     TEASER-BANNER DATE LOGIC
     Populates the Roman and Yahuah dates in the today-comparison
     banner. Keep MONTH_STARTS in sync with /calendar/today.
     ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<script is:inline>
(function() {
  'use strict';

  var MONTH_STARTS = {
    aviv:     '2026-03-19',
    month_2:  '2026-04-18',
    month_3:  '2026-05-17',
    month_4:  '2026-06-15',
    month_5:  '2026-07-15',
    month_6:  '2026-08-13',
    month_7:  '2026-09-11',
    month_8:  '2026-10-11',
    month_9:  '2026-11-10',
    month_10: '2026-12-09',
    month_11: '2027-01-08',
    month_12: '2027-02-07',
    month_13: '2027-03-09'
  };

  var dayNames = ['Sunday','Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday'];
  var monthNames = ['January','February','March','April','May','June',
                    'July','August','September','October','November','December'];
  var monthLabels = ['Aviv','Month 2','Month 3','Month 4','Month 5','Month 6',
                     'Month 7','Month 8','Month 9','Month 10','Month 11','Month 12','Month 13'];
  var monthKeys = ['aviv','month_2','month_3','month_4','month_5','month_6',
                   'month_7','month_8','month_9','month_10','month_11','month_12','month_13'];

  var today = new Date();
  var dayName = dayNames[today.getDay()];
  var romanDate = monthNames[today.getMonth()] + ' ' + today.getDate();

  var romanEl = document.getElementById('banner-roman-date');
  if (romanEl) romanEl.textContent = dayName + ', ' + romanDate;

  var todayDate = new Date(today.getFullYear(), today.getMonth(), today.getDate());
  todayDate.setHours(0,0,0,0);

  var yahsLabel = '—';
  if (MONTH_STARTS.aviv) {
    var avivStart = new Date(MONTH_STARTS.aviv);
    avivStart.setHours(0,0,0,0);

    if (todayDate >= avivStart) {
      var currentMonthIndex = 0;
      var currentMonthStart = avivStart;

      for (var i = 1; i < monthKeys.length; i++) {
        if (!MONTH_STARTS[monthKeys[i]]) break;
        var thisStart = new Date(MONTH_STARTS[monthKeys[i]]);
        thisStart.setHours(0,0,0,0);
        if (todayDate < thisStart) break;
        currentMonthIndex = i;
        currentMonthStart = thisStart;
      }

      var msPerDay = 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24;
      var dayOfMonth = Math.floor((todayDate - currentMonthStart) / msPerDay) + 1;
      yahsLabel = monthLabels[currentMonthIndex] + ', Day ' + dayOfMonth;
    }
  }

  var yahsEl = document.getElementById('banner-yahs-date');
  if (yahsEl) yahsEl.textContent = yahsLabel;
})();
</script>

<style>
  /* ─── Page wrap ─── */
  .cal-landing {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0905 0%, #1a110a 25%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #b8a584;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.75rem 6rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ─── Teaser banner (today comparison) ─── */
  .today-banner {
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    max-width: 960px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
    background:
      linear-gradient(
        90deg,
        rgba(107, 68, 35, 0.22) 0%,
        rgba(107, 68, 35, 0.18) 48%,
        rgba(70, 100, 145, 0.18) 52%,
        rgba(70, 100, 145, 0.22) 100%
      );
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    transition: border-color 0.25s, transform 0.25s, box-shadow 0.25s;
  }

  .today-banner:hover {
    border-color: rgba(212, 161, 74, 0.5);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }

  .today-banner-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.6rem 2rem;
  }

  .today-banner-side {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .today-banner-side.roman { align-items: flex-start; }
  .today-banner-side.yahs  { align-items: flex-end; }

  .today-banner-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.65;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .today-banner-side.roman .today-banner-label { color: #D4924A; }
  .today-banner-side.yahs  .today-banner-label { color: #9BB5DA; }

  .today-banner-value {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: 0.015em;
  }

  .today-banner-side.roman .today-banner-value { color: #D4924A; }
  .today-banner-side.yahs  .today-banner-value { color: #9BB5DA; }

  .today-banner-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .today-banner-cta-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(244, 236, 219, 0.6);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .today-banner-cta-line {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #F4ECDB;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .today-banner-cta-arrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #D4A14A;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }

  .today-banner:hover .today-banner-cta-arrow { color: #F4ECDB; }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .today-banner-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.1rem;
      padding: 1.4rem 1.4rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .today-banner-side.roman,
    .today-banner-side.yahs {
      align-items: center;
    }
  }

  /* ─── Hero ─── */
  .cal-hero {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto 5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cal-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a7855;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cal-eyebrow.with-rules::before,
  .cal-eyebrow.with-rules::after {
    content: "—";
    margin: 0 0.7em;
    color: #6a5840;
  }

  .cal-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    letter-spacing: 0.025em;
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin: 1.4rem 0 1.4rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cal-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    color: #b8a584;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─── Section heads ─── */
  .cal-block { max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .cal-block + .cal-block { margin-top: 3.5rem; }

  .cal-section-head {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .cal-section-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 3vw, 2.15rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0.9rem 0 0.85rem;
  }

  .cal-section-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #b8a584;
    max-width: 580px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* ─── Luminary cards (3-up) ─── */
  .luminary-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.6rem;
  }

  .luminary-card {
    position: relative;
    background: #1a110a;
    border: 1px solid rgba(180, 140, 80, 0.18);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2.25rem 1.85rem 1.7rem;
    transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s, transform 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .luminary-card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 2px;
  }

  .lum-sun::before   { background: #d4a04a; }
  .lum-moon::before  { background: #8aa4c4; }
  .lum-stars::before { background: #9678b8; }

  .luminary-card:hover {
    background: #221710;
    border-color: rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.34);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .card-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: #8a7855;
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .luminary-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .luminary-card > p {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    color: #b8a584;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 1.7rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .read-link {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: #c9a961;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .luminary-card:hover .read-link { color: #f0e0bf; }

  /* ─── Decorative divider ─── */
  .cal-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 5rem auto 4rem;
    color: #a88b4f;
    max-width: 520px;
  }

  .cal-divider::before,
  .cal-divider::after {
    content: "";
    height: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.34), transparent);
  }

  .cal-divider .glyph {
    margin: 0 1.4rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.5em;
  }

  /* ─── Category cards (4×3 grid) ─── */
  .category-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.15rem;
  }

  .cat-card {
    position: relative;
    background: #1a110a;
    border: 1px solid rgba(180, 140, 80, 0.18);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.7rem 1.5rem 1.4rem;
    transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s, transform 0.2s, opacity 0.25s;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    min-height: 240px;
  }

  .cat-card:hover {
    background: #221710;
    border-color: rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.34);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .cat-card-pending { opacity: 0.62; }
  .cat-card-pending:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .roman {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #a88b4f;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cat-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    letter-spacing: 0.025em;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cat-card > p {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    color: #b8a584;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    flex: 1;
    margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
  }

  .study-count {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: #a88b4f;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  /* ─── Responsive ─── */
  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .category-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .luminary-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .category-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .cal-landing { padding: 3.25rem 1.1rem 4rem; }
    .category-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cal-block + .cal-block { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
    .cal-divider { margin: 3.5rem auto 3rem; }
  }
</style>
